1. Validate node installation
% node -v

2. Create react app
% npx create-react-app app-name

3. create backend folder
% mkdir backend

4. install package.json
% git init -y

5. install dependancies
express- nodeJS webframe work 
cors- allows ajax requests to skip same origin policy and access remote host 
dotenv - loads enviro variables
mongoose- allows simplier interaction between mongodb and NodeJS
nodemon- restarts node app when file changes are detected

6. create server.js file in backend
7. create .env file 
8. add server.js middleware and db connection
9. add uri to .env
10. add models schema
11. add routes
12. connect server.js to routes
13. postman test 
